issues.title: Separate Validation and Cleaning of Input
WP 3.5 Causes Multiple "Updated" messages
issues.body: The options pages added with this plugin get two "settings updated" messages.

issues.title: Fields Should Support Help Text
issues.body: Give the fields a 'help' argument that displays some help text below the field.

issues.title: All Fields Should Support Default Values
issues.body: Allow the 'default' argument to work on all fields.

commit.message:
Fix a Deprecation Warning on Editor Fields

`wp_editor` no longer accepted fields with brackets in their IDs.
Give the tabs a bit of padding
Make sure the attachment field works with images with only a single size
Remove XML RPC disabling

Unique Frame IDs and Check Media Enqueue

Since we could have multiple frames on a given page, this gives each
media "frame" or "view" its own unique ID.

Also adds a check to make sure `wp_enqueue_media` has only been called
once.

See: http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/22843

This is fixed in WP 3.5.1 beta at the time of writing, but since this
library should play nice with the current major version we'll keep in
the check.
Make the media buttons work again
Merge branch 'master' of git://github.com/AgencyPMG/PMG-WP-Core

Change Default Comment Status Callback

Use a custom callback for default comment status instead of just
`__return_zero`.  Now depends on the `comments_allowed` method.

Reported By: Ricky Cadden
Merge branch 'master' of git://github.com/AgencyPMG/PMG-WP-Core
Separate icon and menu icon and add position to admin pages

Deal with Empty Prefixes for Settings Fields

If there's a settings field object with a prefix, don't prepend and
underscore.  This helps with porting old code to PMGCore.
No need to wrap with a paragraph
